    "title": "Frontend Developer 20260227",
    "description": "Role Summary: Entry-level Frontend Developer position available for a dynamic and creative team. The ideal candidate will have strong foundational skills in web development languages and frameworks with the potential to grow into more complex roles within our technology stacks quickly.\nKey Responsibilities: - Build user interfaces using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React JS, SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS), MySQL Workbench or similar tools for data management; maintain accessibility standards and design best practices throughout the development process.\n- Collaborate with backend developers to ensure seamless integration of frontend components into applications as per architectural requirements.\n- Continuously improve user experience by identifying performance bottlenecks, implementing efficient code structures that optimize speed without compromising on visual appeal or functionality; troubleshoot and debug issues arisen in the development process with effective solutions to maintain high standards of quality assurance.;\nRequired Qualifications: - Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Electronics Engineering, etc. (alternatively equivalent experience)\n- Proficient knowledge of programming languages including but not limited HTML5, CSS3 , JavaScript ES6+ and React JS; familiarity with backend technologies like NodeJS or Python Flask for integration testing purposes is an added advantage.;\n- Experience working on frontend projects using at least three among the four major web development frameworks listed above (React.js/Vue, Angular).",
